  - Pre-fill user data; allow concierge escalation notes.
  - Ability to attach internal notes visible to admins only.
  - Route to appropriate teams (General vs Concierge) with permissions.
- Admin routing:
  - Support ticket list, detail view, status updates, internal notes, export to CSV.
  - Ability to send templated responses via email (selected template version, substitutions).

7) Admin & Role-Based Access
- Roles: Guest (authenticated regular user), Host (authenticated listings), Concierge (admin).
- Admin panel access to all inquiries, status updates, internal notes, email templates, and export features.
- Ensure all admin actions are audit-logged.

8) Data Models & Tables
- EmailTemplate: id, name, locale, version, status (Draft/Published/Archived), subject, htmlBody, textBody, substitutionsSchema (JSON), createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy, updatedBy.
- EmailTemplateVersion: id, templateId, version, subject, htmlBody, textBody, substitutionsSchema, createdAt, author.
- EmailJob (Queue): id, templateId, payload (JSON), to, from, status (Queued/Sending/Delivered/Failed/Suppressed), attempts, nextAttempt, lastError, createdAt, updatedAt.
- EmailDeliveryEvent: id, jobId, eventType (delivered/bounced/dropped/complaint), timestamp, details (JSON).
- SuppressionList: id, email, reason, source (SendGrid/Manual), addedAt, expiresAt (optional).
- UserEmailPreference: userId, unsubscribedAt, globalPreferences (JSON).
- SupportInquiry: id, guestId (nullable), name, email, category, subject, message, status, assignedTo, createdAt, updatedAt, internalNotes (array).
- SupportInquiryMessage: id, inquiryId, sender (Guest/Concierge), message, createdAt, attachments (optional).
- PaymentLinkRecord: id, inquiryId, link, expiresAt, status, createdAt, updatedAt.
- ReceiptRecord: id, orderId, userId, amount, currency, data (JSON), sentAt, status.

- Ensure runtime safety: use data ?? [] where results are arrays; guard with Array.isArray() when mapping; use useState<Type[]>([]) defaults.

9) APIs & Routes
- Email Templates
