## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Kit alignment: adhere to the Roam Resort design system provided (colors, typography, cards, nav, layout, spacing).
- Email Template Admin
  - List, search, filter by locale/status.
  - Create/Edit form with rich HTML editor or templated fields; validate substitutions.
  - Preview modal with sample payloads per locale.
  - Version history view with diff (optional) and ability to revert.
- Email Preview & Testing
  - Admin can send test email to a configurable address.
  - Preview values: subject, body (HTML/text).
- Contact / Support Page
  - Public form with validation (name, email, category, subject, message).
  - Authenticated form with prefilled user data and internal notes field.
  - Client-side form validation; show inline errors; spinners on submit.
  - Success confirmation screen with reference number and suggested next steps.
- Admin Support
  - List of inquiries with statuses; detail view with conversation thread; update status; add internal notes.
  - CSV export of inquiries.
- Security & Validation
  - Use proper authentication checks for admin routes.
  - Validate all inputs; sanitize HTML in email templates to prevent injection.
  - Ensure unsubscribe state is respected in frontend forms (do not include unsubscribed addresses in sending).

### Backend
- Database
  - Implement data models described above with appropriate relations.
  - Ensure nullable fields are handled safely; use default values where applicable.
- Email Engine
  - Integrate with SendGrid:
    - Send transactional templates with substitutions.
    - Support locale-based templates.
  - Implement queue with retries:
    - Exponential backoff; max attempts threshold.
    - Move to Failed after max attempts; emit admin alert.
  - Scrubbing and suppression:
    - Respect unsubscribe flags; check suppression lists before sending.
  - Webhooks:
    - Consume SendGrid events; update EmailJob status; add to suppression if unsubscribe event.
- Template Versioning
  - Create new Version on update; mark previous as archived if necessary.
  - Ensure preview uses the latest Published or selected version.
- Support & Contact
  - Persist inquiries and messages; route to concierge/admin as appropriate.
  - Notify via email using templates when new inquiries arrive or status changes.
- Payments & Receipts
  - Generate payment links (Stripe Connect) and store link state.
  - Upon payment completion, trigger receipt email using Receipt template.
- Security
  - Authenticate all admin endpoints; authorize based on roles.
  - Validate payloads strictly; use schema validation (e.g., zod/joi) and return clear errors.
- Logging & Observability
  - Structured logs for email events, template rendering, queue processing.
  - Admin dashboards for email send metrics, bounce rates, and suppression counts.

### Integration
- Ensure front-end components call backend APIs with consistent shapes.
- Use data normalization and safe access patterns:
  - const items = data ?? [];
  - Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [];
- Use React useState([]) for array-based state; initialize with proper types.
- All API responses validated on the client:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- All optional data accessed with optional chaining.

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Guest registers or logs in.
2) Guest submits an inquiry via the Inquiry Flow:
   - Guest fills stay details, dates, guests, notes.
   - On submission, an Inquiry record is created; EmailJob enqueued using inquiry_confirmation template.
   - Concierge is notified; status appears in Admin panel.
3) Concierge reviews inquiry in Admin:
   - Update status (New -> Contacted -> Deposit Paid -> Confirmed).
   - Add internal notes; optionally trigger payment link/template.
   - If payment required, send payment link email via EmailJob.
4) Guest receives confirmation email with details and next steps.
5) If payment occurs via Stripe Connect:
   - Receipt email is sent automatically on success; status update reflected to Concierge.
6) Support / Contact Form:
   - Public users submit general questions or concierge requests.
   - Admin staff respond via email templates; thread stored in SupportInquiry with messages.
7) Unsubscribe / Bounce:
   - If a recipient unsubscribes or bounces, the system adds to suppression and stops sending further transactional emails unless overridden by explicit opt-in exceptions.

---

