# Email Notifications & Templates

## Overview
Build a robust email notification system with transactional templates for signup verification, inquiry confirmations, concierge messages, payment links, and receipts. Include template versioning, preview tooling for admins, sending queue with retry logic, unsubscribe/bounce handling, and suppression lists. Expose a public and authenticated Contact / Support Form to submit general questions or concierge requests, tied into the same notification workflow where applicable. Ensure frontend, backend, and admin tooling integrate with the existing Roam Resort platform design system and security model.

---

## Components to Build

1) Email Template Engine & Template Library
- Purpose: Create, version, test, and render transactional emails with substitution variables.
- Features:
  - Template creation with versioning (Draft, Published, Archived).
  - Variables and substitution tokens (e.g., {{guestName}}, {{inquiryId}}, {{paymentLink}}, {{receiptId}}).
  - Preview UI in admin for each version with sample data.
  - Localization hooks (support multiple locales per template).
  - Global header/footer blocks reusable across templates.
  - Template rendering in backend for sending and in UI for previews.
- Data surfaces: template metadata (id, name, locale, version, status), content body (HTML/text), substitutions schema, lastUpdated, createdBy.

2) Email Sending Service (Queue, Retry, Suppression)
- Purpose: Reliable delivery with retry/backoff and suppression management.
- Features:
  - Send grid integration (transactional emails) with templated content and substitution variables.
  - Job queue (e.g., Redis-based) with retry policy (exponential backoff, max attempts).
  - Bounce handling and suppression lists (hard bounces, unsubscribe events, global suppression).
  - Rate limiting to comply with SendGrid guidelines.
  - Fallback mechanism to plain text if HTML rendering fails.
  - Admin visibility: per-email status (Queued, Sending, Delivered, Bounced, Failed, Suppressed).
- Data surfaces: queue entries (id, templateId, payload, attempts, status, nextAttempt, createdAt, updatedAt), delivery events, suppression lists.

3) Transactional Email Flows
-.signup_verification: Send after user registers, with verification link or code.
- inquiry_confirmation: Acknowledge guest inquiry submission with details.
- concierge_message: Internal messages to and from concierge with placeholders for agent notes.
- payment_link: Send Stripe Connect payment link (or placeholder) when concierge triggers payment.
- receipt_email: Send post-payment receipt with transaction details.

- For each flow:
  - Define required substitutions, min data shapes, and fallback behavior if data is missing.
  - Include logic to respect unsubscribe status and suppression lists.
  - Include audit logging: who triggered, timestamp, template version used.

